OL,3,CStore owner speaks out after 30%
OL,4,Cincrease in shoplifting in the West
OL,5,CMidlands
OL,7,FLast week the government promised to
OL,8,Fintroduce stronger measures to tackle
OL,9,Fshoplifting, and though this will be
OL,10,Fwelcomed by shop owners, many in the
OL,11,FMidlands say that things must change
OL,12,Fnow.
OL,14,FIn a statement, West Midlands Police
OL,15,FSuperintendent Lisa Jayne-Robson said:
OL,1,W~+$ ~sh7}h7sj5 ~{4~k4k4          G5/8
